    "Both parameters represent user tension, and physical arousal.",
    "HR and EDA biosensors are both low cost and non-intrusive for users.",
    "In contrast, the EEG sensors can extract very useful data to understand brainwaves, but those data are difficult to interpret, and the devices are uncomfortable for users to wear.",
    "Finally, eye tracking and electromyography are the least frequently used techniques with which to measure physiological parameters.",
    "Interestingly, there were few experiences with eye tracking (5.1%), even though the HMD equipment can do so."
